<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}-{6}{y}={34}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{2}{y}=-{38}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --8. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{8}}{{4}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{8}}}{{4}}{\left({4}{x}+-{6}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{8}}}{{4}}{\left({34}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{8}\right)}{x}+-{12}{y}={68}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{2}{y}=-{38}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{30}}{{-{{10}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+-{6}{\left(-{3}\right)}={34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{\left({18}\right)}={34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}={34}-{\left({18}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{16}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

